deployment_site: East Antarctica, Area IV, Wilkes Land
comments: Whale Lander tag as used by R Andrews on short-finned pilot whales in HI for the remote-release proxy tests, but with short darts (5.0 cm total length, one row of petals with petals cut back to approximately 12 mm long), but rebatteried by WC in December

deployment_site: East Antarctica, Area V, Terre Adelie
comments: LIMPET SPLASH10-292B (AM-292B with 2-lay antenna) and Peridot Rev. 4  8cm darts; attached to urethane deployment cup with 70cm of Aqua-solve tape. Arranged in barrel with long axis perpendicular to long axis of whale and antenna high, line drawn between darts is parallel to long axis of body
